{"questionId":"9076602","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Hydrogen atoms in an ultraviolet (UV) lamp make transitions from the first excited state to the ground state. Photons are emitted and are incident on a photoelectric surface as shown.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4802/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_12.49.40.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/08\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The electric potential of the photoelectric surface is 0 V. The variable voltage is adjusted so that the collecting plate is at –1.2 V.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/5e294f09e6c7b101d4d230cc4ee7871457f54f0f.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>An electron is emitted from the photoelectric surface with kinetic energy 2.1 eV. Calculate the speed of the electron at the collecting plate.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>kinetic energy at collecting plate =&nbsp;0.9&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>eV<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>speed =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{2 \\times 0.9 \\times 1.6 \\times {{10}^{ - 19}}}}{{9.11 \\times {{10}^{ - 31}}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>0.9</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>1.6</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>19</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>9.11</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>31</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong>&nbsp;= 5.6 × 10<sup>5</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>ms<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow ECF from MP1</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076602","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ1.c.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An electron is emitted from the photoelectric surface with kinetic energy 2.1 eV. Calculate the speed of the electron at the collecting plate.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}